{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"FragmentDirective","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FragmentDirective","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.FragmentDirective"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li class=\"section\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/URL_Fragment_Text_Directives\">URL Fragment Text Directives</a></li><li class=\"section\"><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FragmentDirective\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>FragmentDirective</code></a></em></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for URL Fragment Text Directives</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/fragmentDirective\"><code>Document.fragmentDirective</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>FragmentDirective</code></strong> interface is an object exposed to allow code to check whether or not a browser supports <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/URI/Fragment/Text_fragments\">text fragments</a>.</p>\n<p>It is accessed via the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/fragmentDirective\"><code>Document.fragmentDirective</code></a> property.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_properties","title":"Instance properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_methods","title":"Instance methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"checking_if_text_fragments_are_supported","title":"Checking if text fragments are supported","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  The code below logs whether or not text fragments are supported in your browser by checking that <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/fragmentDirective\"><code>Document.fragmentDirective</code></a> is defined.\n  Note that the object is empty, and at present is mainly intended for feature detection.\n  In the future, it might include other information.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html hidden notranslate\"><code>&lt;pre id=\"log\"&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js hidden notranslate\"><code>const logElement = document.querySelector(\"#log\");\nfunction log(text) {\n  logElement.innerText = text;\n}\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: css hidden notranslate\"><code>#log {\n  height: 20px;\n}\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><div class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></div><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>if (document.fragmentDirective) {\n  log(\"Your browser supports text fragments.\");\n} else {\n  log(\"Text fragments are not supported in your browser.\");\n}\n</code></pre></div><div class=\"code-example\"><div class=\"example-header\"></div><iframe class=\"sample-code-frame\" title=\"Checking if text fragments are supported sample\" id=\"frame_checking_if_text_fragments_are_supported\" width=\"100%\" height=\"60\" src=\"about:blank\" data-live-path=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FragmentDirective\" data-live-id=\"checking_if_text_fragments_are_supported\" sandbox=\"allow-same-origin allow-scripts\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/scroll-to-text-fragment/#fragmentdirective","title":"URL Fragment Text Directives"}],"query":"api.FragmentDirective"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.FragmentDirective"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::target-text\"><code>::target-text</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Instance properties","id":"instance_properties"},{"text":"Instance methods","id":"instance_methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The FragmentDirective interface is an object exposed to allow code to check whether or not a browser supports text fragments.","popularity":0,"modified":null,"other_translations":[],"pageType":"web-api-interface","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/fragmentdirective","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/fragmentdirective/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/null","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"FragmentDirective","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FragmentDirective","title":"FragmentDirective"}],"pageTitle":"FragmentDirective - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false},"url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FragmentDirective"}